#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
=============================================================================
 Script      : apply_repo_governance.py
 Purpose     : Apply the standard SBIePay repo governance baseline to GitLab
               application repositories (ITEPAYPG-SBIePay2).

 WHAT IT DOES (each step is an independent, commentable section):
   Step 1  Group Invites        - share repo with the LDAP groups at set roles
   Step 2  Push Rules           - branch-name + commit-message regex
   Step 3  Protected Branches   - main / develop / release/* ; push = No one
   Step 4  MR Approval Rules    - one rule per approver group, per branch
   Step 5  Pipelines Must Pass  - only_allow_merge_if_pipeline_succeeds = true
   Step 6  Merge Method         - "Merge commit" only  (no FF / no semi-linear)
   Step 7  Squash Option        - "Do not allow"
   Step 8  Default Branch       - set to 'main'

   Steps 5-8 are each in their OWN function and their OWN call line in
   run_one(). To DISABLE any of them, comment out its single call line in
   run_one() (they are clearly marked). Nothing else needs to change.

 SCOPE / SAFETY:
   - Every WRITE call targets /projects/<resolved-id>/... ONLY.
   - Group lookups are READ-ONLY (GET) to resolve group IDs.
   - No group/subgroup object is ever modified. Listing a subgroup's projects
     (--subgroup) is a READ-ONLY GET; the writes still go per-project.
   - Idempotent: every step checks current state first and skips if already
     correct, so re-running is safe and makes no redundant changes.

 Dependencies: NONE - Python standard library only (no pip required).
               Python 3.6+ / RHEL air-gapped compatible.

 TARGET SELECTION (choose exactly one):
   --project <id-or-path>   ONE repo.        e.g. --project 2823
                                             e.g. --project group/sub/repo
   --subgroup <id-or-path>  ALL repos under a subgroup, including nested
                            sub-subgroups.   e.g. --subgroup itepaypg-sbiepay2/application/backend
   --batch <file>           Repos listed in a text file, one ID/path per line
                            ('#' comments and blank lines ignored).
   (none)                   Falls back to TARGET_PROJECT in CONFIG below.

 MODES:
   (default)   APPLY   - make the changes, then auto-verify.
   --dry-run           - print every write that WOULD happen. Changes nothing.
   --verify            - read current state only. Changes nothing.

 MULTI-REPO BEHAVIOUR:
   --subgroup and --batch run repos in order and STOP on the first error
   (fail-stop), so a bad config cannot silently propagate. Repos completed
   before the failure are listed in the summary so you know where to resume.

 OUTPUT:
   Console                             - live log
   governance_<repo>_<ts>.txt          - single-repo run log
   governance_BATCH_<ts>.txt           - consolidated log for --batch/--subgroup

 TYPICAL USAGE:
   1. Set TOKEN and GITLAB_URL in the CONFIG block below.
   2. Preview one repo:
        python3 apply_repo_governance.py --project 2823 --dry-run
   3. Apply one repo, then check the VERIFY block it prints:
        python3 apply_repo_governance.py --project 2823
   4. Preview a whole subgroup:
        python3 apply_repo_governance.py --subgroup itepaypg-sbiepay2/application/backend --dry-run
   5. Apply the subgroup:
        python3 apply_repo_governance.py --subgroup itepaypg-sbiepay2/application/backend
   6. Re-check anytime (read-only):
        python3 apply_repo_governance.py --project 2823 --verify

 TOKEN REQUIREMENTS:
   Personal Access Token (NOT a group/project access token) from a user with
   Maintainer (40) or Owner (50) on the target projects, scope = 'api'.
   Group access tokens are rejected by the push_rule endpoint (403).
=============================================================================
"""

